    "industry":       "Creative",
    "notes":          "Dribbble uses a near-black (#0d0c22) + hot pink (#ea4c89) brand palette. The font is 'Mona Sans' (GitHub's variable font). The site relies on a 4-column masonry grid of shot thumbnails — design is deliberately minimal to let user work shine. Pill-shaped buttons (border-radius: 9999px) are a signature element. The Shoelace web component library underpins many UI components with a comprehensive --sl-color-* token system. Hover states reveal muted purple (#7b7194) on nav links."
